article.headline: North Texas 66, New Orleans 60
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Ty Thomas scored 13 points to help North Texas defeat New Orleans 66-60 on Thursday night. Jeffrey Simpson and Leonard Hopkins each scored 12 for North Texas (10-7, 3-3 Sun Belt), which came back after trailing 29-25 at halftime. Bo McCalebb led New Orleans (8-11, 3-3) with 25 points. North Texas won the rebounding battle 40-32 and outshot New Orleans 45.3 percent to 41.4 percent. New Orleans was hurt by 1-of-10 3-point shooting in the second half. North Texas attempted only seven 3-pointers all game, instead looking to score inside. The Mean Green scored 15 points at the foul line, compared to five points on free throws for New Orleans. <
